        </tr>
      </thead>

      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <th scope="row">Engagement</th>
          <td></td>
        </tr>

        <tr>
          <th scope="row">Maintenance</th>
          <td></td>
        </tr>

        <tr>
          <th scope="row">Retention</th>
          <td>
            <ul>
              <li>
                Frame against the leading edge (often the knee/shin or
                shoulder/upper arm), then mobilize your hips to reset your angle
              </li>

              <li>
                If your hips get turned, maintain posture by turning your torso
                to match
              </li>
            </ul>
